title: Bookended by tragedy, Biden's storied career nears the end
text: > Top News Bookended by tragedy, Biden's storied career nears the end FILE - In this June 6, 2015, file photo, Hunter Biden, left, kisses his nephew Hunter, son of Beau Biden, as they stand with Beau's widow Hallie, third from left, Vice President Joe Biden and Beau's daughter Natalie before his funeral, at St. Anthony of Padua Roman Catholic Church in Wilmington, Del. Biden, the eldest son of the vice president, died of brain cancer May 30 at age 46. Biden's storied political career will end much the way it started nearly half a century ago: shaped by crushing personal tragedy that shook his confidence in his own ability to lead. In deciding not to run for president, Biden has turned away from months of preparations and countless hours that had put him on the verge of a third presidential campaign. (AP Photo/Patrick Semansky, File)
